&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scale manufacturing processes from R&amp;amp;D prototype builds to higher volume and fieldable manufacturing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interface with mechanical and electrical design engineers during product development for DfM &amp;amp; DfA considerations, to ensure a smoother transition to manufacturing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create, evaluate, and improve manufacturing processes&amp;nbsp;applying knowledge of product design, fabrication, assembly, tooling, and materials&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and document manufacturing procedures, work instructions, setup sheets, safety processes, routers, inspection points, and QC documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and implement manufacturing processes including process definition, PFMEA, equipment definition and selection, layout planning, integration coordination, startup, qualification, and training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with technicians to ensure manufacturing processes are being followed and implemented correctly and safely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify and implement process improvements for yield, quality, throughput, or other KPI as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Utilize analytical skills to perform root cause investigation analysis and provide recommendations for corrective and preventative actions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employ QA skills to complete acceptance testing, identify &amp;amp; prevent production defects, and develop QA processes for efficient manufacturing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
